text:
I'm 36, kind and thoughtful, open-minded, intelligent, neither a mover nor a shaker yet still quietly ambitious, a design student, living alone, and--because I know you care--reasonably attractive.

I also:

am terribly low-maintenance and find joy in the simplest things, and only occasionally demanding (mostly of myself... I am not fond of mediocrity);

can be a bit of a loner, though I cherish time spent with friends;

have a pretty well-developed sense of humor (which sometimes veers toward the dark and cynical, but I'm a compassionate person I swear);

enjoy listening to music--both live (almost exclusively at smaller venues) and recorded;

value creativity and spirituality (among other things of course--I just happen to be focused on these two things at the moment).

I'm absolutely not looking for anything serious right away. I would like someone to spend time with, have a few beers with, go to shows or movies with, listen to records with--you get the idea. I'm not hung up on what you possess, what you do (as long as it's legal), or physical attributes that you have no control over (though I think you should find yourself attractive and take care of yourself).

I do prefer that you be around my age, relatively stable, and easy-going. Bonus points if you can make people laugh, work with your hands (even as an avocation), have a knack for storytelling, have great taste in music, or love garage/rummage sales. 

Photos are appreciated, will be treated with care, and of course will be reciprocated if I think we might be a good match.

*Please do not respond if you are married/partnered*

...insatiably curious;
...adorkable (a cross between dorky and adorable) -- or so I have been told;
...wondering where you are and why I haven't found you yet;
...very interested in long term things -- perennials, years-long friendships and romances, old houses, antiques, your childhood memories;
...a good listener;
...small, quiet, and intense;
...unconventionally conventional;
...loyal.

You are...

...tolerant of other people's foibles, even if they're annoying;
...a father;
...strong willed;
...physically fit;
...monogamous, even if it's a struggle;
...smart as hell, so smart you realize the older you get, the less you know.

No married men, please.

It took me a while to realize that having a relationship that's truly bonded strong is a good way to end my depression that I have been suffering with for so long. Maybe you can help me? ^-^ Please be clean and disease free. No older than 33. Also please have transportation. If you love thick girls and can sweep a girl off her feet, that's a huge bonus (;

Pic4Pic

Please leave your name, age and description of yourself so I know that your not a robot lol xD Hope to talk to you soon (:

...tell me everything;
...listen to everything;
...kiss, spoon, lick the inside of my knee;
...find out what happens at the end of "Damages;"
...read a novel every once in a while and talk about it afterwards;
...plan the rest of his life even if it never turns out that way;
...be fair and get fairness back;
...stay fit until he's 90;
...believe the best in people;
...think big picture;
...come and find me, soon!
